b'' b'' b'............................................................................' b"crypto conference announcement final call for papers" b'............................................................................' b'' b'the thirteenth annual crypto conference, sponsored by the international' b'association for cryptologic research (iacr), in cooperation with' b'the ieee computer society technical committee on security and privacy,' b'the computer science department of the university of california, santa' b'barbara, and bell-northern research (a subsidiary of northern telecom),' b'will be held on the campus of the university of california, santa barbara,' b'on august original research papers and technical expository talks' b'are solicited on all practical and theoretical aspects of cryptology. it is' b'anticipated that some talks may also be presented by special invitation of the' b'program committee.' b'-------------------------' b'instructions for authors: authors are requested to send copies of a' b'detailed abstract (not a full paper) by april to the program chair' b'at the address given below. a limit of pages of 12pt type (not counting' b'the bibliography or the title page) is placed on all submissions. submissions' b'must arrive on time or be postmarked no later than april and sent by' b'airmail in order to receive consideration by the program committee. it is' b'required that submissions start with a succinct statement of the problem' b'addressed, the solution proposed, and its significance to cryptology,' b'appropriate for a non-specialist reader. technical development directed to' b'the specialist should follow as needed.' b'-------------------------' b'abstracts that have been submitted to other conferences that have proceedings' b'are not eligible for submission.' b'' b'submissions must be anonymous. this means that names and affiliations of' b'authors should only appear on the title page of the submission; it should' b'be possible to remove this page and send the papers to program committee' b'members. a latex style file that produces output in this format is available by email from the program chair.' b'' b'authors will be informed of acceptance or rejection in a letter mailed on' b'or before june a compilation of all accepted abstracts will be' b'available at the conference in the form of pre-proceedings. authors of' b'accepted abstracts will be allowed to submit revised versions for the' b'pre-proceedings. a revised abstract should contain only minor changes and' b'corrections to the originally submitted abstract. all revised abstracts must' b'be received by the program chair by july the page limit will be' b'strictly enforced for the pre-proceedings.' b'' b'complete conference proceedings are expected to be published in springer-' b"verlag's lecture notes in computer science series at a later date, pending" b'negotiation.' b'-------------------------' b'the program committee consists of' b'' b'd. stinson (chair, nebraska)' b'm. bellare (ibm t. j. watson) e. biham (technion, israel)' b'e. brickell (sandia national labs) j. feigenbaum (at&t bell labs)' b'r. impagliazzo (ucsd) a. odlyzko (at&t bell labs)' b't. okamoto (ntt, japan) b. pfitzmann (hildesheim, germany)' b'r. rueppel (r3, switzerland) s. vanstone (waterloo, canada)' b'-------------------------' b'send submissions to the program chair:' b'' b"douglas r. stinson, crypto b'computer science and engineering department' b'115 ferguson hall, university of nebraska' b'lincoln, ne usa' b'telephone: b'fax: b'' b'for other information, contact the general chair:' b'' b"paul c. van oorschot, crypto b'bell-northern research (mail stop b'3500 carling ave.' b'nepean, ontario k2h 8e9 canada' b'telephone: b'fax: b'' b'............................................................................' b"crypto general information (august b'............................................................................' b'' b"the program: crypto'93 is the thirteenth in a